BMI.LongName: Body mass index (rounded to nearest integer

handedness.Description: Whether someone is left-handed, right-handed, or ambidextrous

Levels.applied: Enrolled at a university of applied sciences

NEO_A.Description: Score on the Agreeableness scale of the NEO-FFI

NEO_C.Description: Score on the Conscientiousness scale of the NEO-FFI

NEO_E.Description: Score on the Extraversion scale of the NEO-FFI

NEO_N.Description: Score on the Neuroticism scale of the NEO-FFI

trial_type.Description: Whether the trial was to match emotion or orientation (=control)

response_accuracy.Description: Whether the response was correct, incorrect, or a miss

response_hand.Description: Which hand was used to respond

sex.LongName: Sex of face images (in case of emotion trial)
sex.Description: Which sex did the presented faces have?

emo_match.LongName: The emotion of the face to match (in case of emotion trials)
emo_match.Description: The emotion of the face to match (in case of emotion trials)?

ori_match.LongName: Orientation of image (in case of control trial)
ori_match.Description: Which orientation did the participants have to match?

ethn_target.Description: Which ethnicity did the target face have?

ethn_match.Description: Which ethnicity did the to-be matched face have?

ethn_distractor.Description: Which ethnicity did the distractor face have?

trial_type.Description: Whether the trial was to match emotion or orientation (=control)

stop_signal_delay.Description: Time in between the onset of the stimulus (face image) and the stop signal

response_accuracy.Description: Whether the response was correct, incorrect, or a miss

response_hand.Description: Which hand was used to respond

sex.LongName: Sex of face images (in case of emotion trial)
sex.Description: Which sex did the presented faces have?

onset.Description: Onset of the trial, i.e., the appearance of the grey screen (duration: 1 sec). Note, this is the onset of the trial. The onset of the different phases is as follows: encoding phase = onset + 1, retention phase = onset + 2, memory/retrieval phase = onset + 4

trial_type.Description: Whether the display was passive (no display), active which changed, or didn't change

Levels.passive: no display with oriented bars, only a grey screen
Levels.active_change: display with oriented bars, which changed relative to the first display
Levels.active_nochange: display with oriented bars, which DIDN'T change relative to the first display

response_time.LongName: Time it took the participant to respond relative to the start of the memory/retrieval phase. To get the onset of the actual response: onset + 4 + response_time

response_accuracy.Description: Whether the response was correct, incorrect, or a miss

response_hand.Description: Which hand was used to respond

README:
The PIOP2 dataset is part of the Amsterdam Open MRI Collection (AOMIC), a collection of multimodal (3T) MRI datasets including structural (T1-weighted), diffusion-weighted, and (resting-state and task-based) functional BOLD MRI data, as well as detailed demographics and psychometric variables from a large set of healthy participants.
This dataset contains both raw and preprocessed data (and other "derivatives"), which is available on [Openneuro](https://openneuro.org/datasets/ds002790).

The contents of this dataset are described in detail in [this preprint](https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.06.16.155317v1). More general information about the AOMIC datasets, including instructions on how to download (parts of) it, check out the [AOMIC website](https://nilab-uva.github.io/AOMIC.github.io/).
